Defendant Thomas C Joers in court with attorney Megan L. Morrisey.  Jesica Ann Ballenger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

 Amended Information filed in open court.  Defense counsel acknowledged receipt of a copy of the Amended Information, waived its reading and entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant.  

Charge amended as follows:

COUNT 1:  THEFT (VALUE NOT EXCEEDING $2,500), contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor

COUNT 2:  CREDIT CARD-FRADULENT USE (<= $2500), contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.41(5)(b), a Class A Misdemeanor

COUNT 3:  DISORDERLY CONDUCT, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 947.01(1), a Class B Misdemeanor 

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea to amended charges.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO ALL COUNTS:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
As to Count 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction with Huber release for employment, medical care/treatment, and school, Consecutive to Count 2 and with any other sentence time being served, with credit for 0 days served. 

As to Count 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction with Huber release for employment, medical care/treatment, and school, Consecutive to Count 1 and with any other sentence time being served, with credit for 0 days served. 

As to Count 3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction with Huber release for employment, medical care/treatment, and school, Concurrent to Count 2, Consecutive with any other sentence time being served, with credit for 0 days served. 


AS TO COUNTS 1, 2, AND 3:
The Court STAYED these sentences and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 18 MONTHS  with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Obtain Mental health assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*No illegal drugs or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with victim Karen P.- subject to modification or cancel at agent discretion and upon request of victim;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Perform 100 hours of community service for no economic benefit/gain;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments 

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $75.00 payable to Karen P.- to be paid first.  The Court orders financial obligations and restitution to be paid by the end of supervision period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.  The Court orders the defendant referred for evaluation for participation in the dosage probation pilot program.  Appeal rights given by the court.  Filed, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
